## The 3-bucket system (early retirement version)

### Bucket 1 — Cash and safety (0-5 years)
- **Accounts:** HYSA, T-bills, short bonds
- **Target at 50:** ~$500,000 (5 years of expenses)
- **Purpose:** Daily living expenses. Never in equities. Refilled by bucket 2 when markets are positive
- T-bills are state and local tax exempt

### Bucket 2 — Growth and stability (5-10 years)
- **Accounts:** Taxable brokerage (index funds, QQQM)
- **Target at 50:** ~$660,000-720,000
- **Purpose:** Balances growth with stability. Harvests gains in up years to refill bucket 1. Left alone in down markets. This is the mechanism that eliminates sequence of return risk

### Bucket 3 — Long-term growth (15+ years, untouched)
- **Accounts:** Roth IRA, Roth 401k
- **Target at 50:** ~$300,000-360,000
- **Purpose:** High equity exposure. Left completely untouched until 67. Compounds tax-free for 17 years
- **Projected at 67 (7% return):** ~$1M+ combined

