**Starting balances:** ~$14,000 each
**Contribution:** Maxed annually ($7,000/person)
**Assumed return:** 7% (S&P 500 long-term average)
**Stop contributing at:** 50 unless part-time or consulting income continues

| Milestone | Person A age | Person B age | Combined Roth |
|-----------|-------------|-------------|---------------|
| Today | 36 | 30 | ~$28,000 |
| Retirement | 50 | 44 | ~$350,000-400,000 |
| Social Security / Roth draw | 67 | 61 | ~$1,000,000-1,100,000 |

**Key insight:** Person B is 6 years younger. Their Roth keeps compounding for 6 additional years after Person A turns 67, significantly extending the combined tax-free pool.

