## Two-phase spending plan

### Phase 1 — Age 50 to 67 (gap years)
- Annual spend: $100,000
- Source: Bucket 1 (cash) and bucket 2 (brokerage)
- Social Security: not claimed yet
- Action: Roth conversions from any traditional IRA while income is low
- No earned income means no new Roth contributions unless part-time or consulting income continues

### Phase 2 — Age 67 onward
- Social Security: $43,000/year
- Roth withdrawals: ~$56,000/year (tax-free)
- Total: ~$99,000/year
- Spending naturally declines ~3%/year (retirement smile curve)

