## Key rules for early retirement

### Roth contribution window
Requires earned income to contribute. Window closes at retirement unless part-time or consulting income continues. Even modest self-employment income keeps both Roth accounts open and contributions flowing.

### Rule of 55
Leaving an employer in the year you turn 55 or later allows penalty-free withdrawals from that employer's 401k only. Does not apply to IRAs or prior 401ks. Not relevant for a retirement at 50.

### 72t (SEPP — Substantially Equal Periodic Payments)
Allows early IRA withdrawals before age 59.5 without the 10% penalty. Requires committing to a fixed IRS-calculated withdrawal schedule for at least 5 years or until 59.5, whichever is longer. Cannot be changed once started. Key tool for bridging ages 50 to 59.5.

